================================================================================
CODE REVIEW FEEDBACK — Cabs Progress Bar (Desktop).js
================================================================================

ISSUE #1 — XSS Risk via innerHTML
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       193
Severity:   HIGH
Code:       p.innerHTML = '<span class="ig-heading-blue">Heading to the airport? </span> Book a cab now ';

Detail:     Using innerHTML introduces an XSS vector. While the current content
            is static, this pattern is dangerous — any future change that
            introduces dynamic/user-supplied data will become exploitable.
            Additionally, innerHTML triggers HTML parser re-parsing of the
            entire element subtree.

Solution:   Use DOM APIs (createElement + textContent) instead:
            
            p.textContent = '';
            var span = document.createElement('span');
            span.className = 'ig-heading-blue';
            span.textContent = 'Heading to the airport? ';
            p.appendChild(span);
            p.appendChild(document.createTextNode(' Book a cab now '));

================================================================================

ISSUE #2 — Unbounded Polling Fallback (Memory Leak / CPU Waste)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Line:       232-234
Severity:   HIGH
Code:       var pollTimer = setInterval(function() {
                if (mount()) clearInterval(pollTimer);
            }, 500);

Detail:     If `mount()` never returns true (e.g., the container element never
            appears on the page), this interval runs forever at 500ms, consuming
            CPU indefinitely. There is no maximum attempt count or timeout.

Solution:   Add a maximum retry count or total elapsed time cap:

            var pollCount = 0;
            var MAX_POLLS = 60; // 30 seconds max
            var pollTimer = setInterval(function() {
                pollCount++;
                if (mount() || pollCount >= MAX_POLLS) clearInterval(pollTimer);
            }, 500);

