ISSUE #6 — External Resources Loaded Without Integrity/Fallback
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Lines:      35-37, 41, 42
Severity:   MEDIUM-HIGH
Code:       iconUrl: "https://www.goindigo.in/content/dam/..."
            var CHECK_ICON = "https://www.goindigo.in/content/dam/..."
            var CIRCLE_ICON = "https://www.goindigo.in/content/dam/..."

Detail:     Images are loaded from a CDN without Subresource Integrity (SRI)
            or error handling. If the CDN is compromised or images are
            unavailable, the UI breaks silently or could serve malicious
            content. No `onerror` fallback is provided for broken images.

Solution:   Add error handlers to image elements:

            img.onerror = function() { this.style.display = 'none'; };

            And consider using inline SVGs or data URIs for critical icons
            to eliminate external dependency.

