ISSUE #7 — Race Condition in mount()
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Lines:      199-215
Severity:   MEDIUM
Code:       function mount() {
                ...
                if (_mounted) { ... return true; }
                ...
                _mounted = true;
                return true;
            }

Detail:     The MutationObserver callback, heartbeat, and resize handler can
            all invoke mount() near-simultaneously. JavaScript is single-
            threaded, but the observer callback can fire between microtasks.
            If `removeInjectedNodes()` runs while the observer detects the
            removal and triggers another mount() synchronously, you can end up
            with duplicate DOM nodes briefly.

Solution:   Add a re-entrancy guard:

            var _mounting = false;
            function mount() {
                if (_mounting) return false;
                _mounting = true;
                try { ... } finally { _mounting = false; }
            }

