ISSUE #8 — Heartbeat Does Not Re-mount After Container Removal
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Lines:      219-225
Severity:   MEDIUM
Code:       if (!container) {
                _mounted = false;
                return;        // <-- returns without attempting re-mount
            }

Detail:     When the container is removed (e.g., SPA navigation), the heartbeat
            sets _mounted = false and returns. It does NOT attempt to re-mount
            on subsequent ticks if the container reappears, because the early
            `if (!_mounted) return;` on line 218 will skip the logic.

Solution:   Remove the early return for `!_mounted` or change the logic to
            attempt mount() when not mounted:

            if (!_mounted) { mount(); return; }

